<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-30T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="44" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4215 Air Pollution/67: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-30T13:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 30,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 2:10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>143. In the absence of Prime Minister this morning presented personally
                            to the Under Secretary of State for External Affairs strong note
                            following your 86 [<hi rend="italic">88</hi>], June 29, 8 p.m.,
                            regarding Trail smelter. Am making every possible effort to arrange
                            precise terms of reference.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>